  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nImplement a new PUT endpoint in the Validator Client (VC) to support updating validator Graffiti in the Siren UI.\r\n\r\nThis is a bit tricky because there are currently multiple ways users can set the Graffiti:\r\n1. [Using the \"--graffiti-file\" flag on the validator client](https://lighthouse-book.sigmaprime.io/graffiti.html#1-using-the---graffiti-file-flag-on-the-validator-client)\r\n2. [Setting the graffiti in the validator_definitions.yml](https://lighthouse-book.sigmaprime.io/graffiti.html#2-setting-the-graffiti-in-the-validator_definitionsyml)\r\n3. [Using the \"--graffiti\" flag on the validator client](https://lighthouse-book.sigmaprime.io/graffiti.html#3-using-the---graffiti-flag-on-the-validator-client)\r\n4. [Using the \"--graffiti\" flag on the beacon node](https://lighthouse-book.sigmaprime.io/graffiti.html#4-using-the---graffiti-flag-on-the-beacon-node)\r\n\r\nIf the endpoint only updates the graffiti in-memory, it would be only temporary and the CLI/file override it when the node gets restated. For this to be persistent, we should probably write the changes to a file, as well as updating the value in-memory.\r\n\r\n@michaelsproul suggested that we should write this to the [validator definitions](https://lighthouse-book.sigmaprime.io/graffiti.html#2-setting-the-graffiti-in-the-validator_definitionsyml), which is guaranteed to exist, and this is also consistent with the other HTTP API methods such as [`feerecipient`](https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/c547a11b0da48db6fdd03bca2c6ce2448bbcc3a9/validator_client/src/http_api/mod.rs#L734-L773). The only source that's higher priority is the `--graffiti-file` flag, so the endpoint could return an error if this value is set, to avoid overriding the changes.\r\n\r\nTo recap, the proposal: \r\n1. Add a new `PUT` Lighthouse API endpoint for updating graffiti, suggested path: `PUT lighthouse/validator/{pub key}/graffiti`\r\n2. The endpoint writes the new graffiti to the `validator_definitions.yml` file for the specified public key\r\n3. Update the validator graffiti in memory\r\n4. If `--graffiti-file` is set, the endpoint should return an error indicating the change failed",
